h3. {color:#d04437}Regarding data security this issue is not resolved yet. Our JIRA instance is used by different clients and its not acceptable that they see epics from projects where they don't have access to. If this issue will not be resolved we unfortunately can't use JIRA anymore.{color}
h3. Steps to reproduce
 # Login to JIRA as an Administrator;
 # Create an Epic in a project;
 # Now create a new issues and choose a different project;
 # Click on the dropdown of the "Epic Link" field;
 # The Epic created before in a different project is listed in this project as well;

h3. What is needed

We want the "Epic Link" field to display only Epics from the selected project.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Server*. Using *JIRA Software Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWCLOUD-17127].
  {panel}

Currently, Kanban and Scrum boards have the feature to right click an issue and select the 'Add flag and comment' and 'Remove flag and add comment' functions that flags the issue as impediment and automatically adds the (flag) icon to the comments, or removes the impediment and automatically adds the (flagoff) icon to the comments, respectively (see screenshots attached).

This feature, however, is not available on the issue view screen. Inside the issue view screen, it is only possible to mark an issue as impediment by manually checking the 'Flagged' field using the edit issue menu, and this does not automatically add the flag icon and comment to the issue as the board function does.

It would be useful if the same feature present in the boards was available inside the issue view screen, perhaps under the 'More' menu. This would speed up flagging and unflagging of issues, and since it is a feature already present in JIRA, it shouldn't be too difficult to make it available from inside the view screen.

h3. Summary

Issue detail view showed up unexpectedly when drag and drop a card on a Kanban board in case that the board filter ordered the issues by a field other than RANK.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a filter which is for ordering issues by a field other than RANK
e.g. {{project = TEST order by duedate}}
# Create a Kanban board with the filter
(i) Please ensure that RANK is not enabled on the board
# Create a card on the board
# Ensure that issue detail view is not shown at this moment
#* If issue detail view is shown, please close it
# Drag the card to another column
## Click *inside* of an element {{span.ghx-inner}} on the card
 !screenshot-2.png|thumbnail! 
## Drag the card to another column
## Drop the card with pointing *outside* of {{span.ghx-inner}}
 !screenshot-3.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Expected Results

Issue detail view should not show up in the board as it didn't with any filter which ordered issues by RANK field.

h3. Actual Results

Issue detail view showed up after drag and drop the card.
 
h3. Notes

When this problem happens, {{event.target}} isn't equal to {{this._mouseDownEvent.target}} in the following code and it seems to cause the problem.

{code}
$.widget("ui.mouse", {
...
	_mouseUp: function(event) {
		$(document)
			.unbind('mousemove.'+this.widgetName, this._mouseMoveDelegate)
			.unbind('mouseup.'+this.widgetName, this._mouseUpDelegate);

		if (this._mouseStarted) {
			this._mouseStarted = false;

			if (event.target == this._mouseDownEvent.target) {
			    $.data(event.target, this.widgetName + '.preventClickEvent', true);
			}

			this._mouseStop(event);
		}

		return false;
	},
...
{code}

h3. Problem Definition

Currently, in JIRA to associate a board with the project, the user will have to add the project name/key in the board filter. If the board filter is something like:

{code}
issuekey in (Bug, Story)
{code}

The board will not be associated with any project. To associate the board with a project, user will have to use board filter like:

{code}
project = Test AND issuekey in (Bug, Story)
{code}


h3. Suggested Solution

This behaviour is not documented in Board documentation. It should be documented in the documentation below:

* [What is a board?|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirasoftwareserver/what-is-a-board-938845235.html]
